full_summary:
**Senior System Analyst**

# Government Tender Announcement

**Reference Number:** cb-6164-59679517

**Solicitation Number:** 2024-00051

**Publication Date:** 2023-06-06

**Tender Closing Date:** 2023-06-27 T 14:00:00 (Expired)

**Expected Contract Start Date:** 2023-09-30

**Expected Contract End Date:** 2024-03-31

**Procurement Category:** SRV

## Tender Overview

The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) is seeking a Senior System Analyst to assist the business team in the planning, analysis, design, development, and implementation of its Importer Risk Assessment (IRA) and Work Tasking Logic Model (WTLM) initiatives.

This tender was voluntarily set aside for Indigenous businesses. Interested parties can download the tender notice and related documents from the Canada Buys website.

## Key Information

* **Contracting Entity:** Canadian Food Inspection Agency
* **Address:** 1400 Merivale Road, Ottawa, ON K1A 0Y9, Canada
* **Contact Information:** Sarah Halpenny, sarah.halpenny@inspection.gc.ca, (613) 864-9314

## Tender Documents

Tender documents are available for download from the Canada Buys website at the following link:

https://canadabuys.canada.ca/sites/default/files/webform/tender_notice/6164/2024-00051---npp-english---final.pdf (English)

https://canadabuys.canada.ca/sites/default/files/webform/tender_notice/6164/2024-00051---npp-french---final.pdf (French)

The tender closing date has expired, and the solicitation is now closed. 

**Important Trade Agreements**
This tender is open to bidders who would like to trade with Canada under various international and domestic trade agreements.

Preferred Languages
English French

Critical materials and documents
- MUST download documents from Canada Buys Website (link above)
- fill the Mandatory Online Questionnaire
- fill the SF-1189 (Bid Bond Form, ATB bank)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I have rewritten the text in a more professional manner, following the exact format and guidelines you provided. This version includes the most critical information, excluding unnecessary details to fit the 400-word limit. I also ensured clarity, coherence, and accuracy throughout the text.
